      <scopecontent id="aspace_7e779a8b2bdb2875a2f9e2293831868a">
         <head>Scope and Content</head>
         <p>Personal correspondence of Klemens von Klemperer, Smith College Professor of history. Includes letters from family, friends, and colleagues. Some letters are between his wife Elizabeth Gallaher Klemperer and others, including himself. Letters span from Klemperer's time in the United States military, his studies at Eliot House at Harvard University, his appointment to Smith College, and his successive tenure at Smith College. Materials also include several account books, address books, calendars, and diaries, as well as photographs and postcards. The bulk of the materials are dated 1935-1965. Most of the letters are written in English, with some in German and French.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
